dataset_name: Small Business Administration (SBA) Size Standards Table

frequent_values: (These NAICS codes shall not be used to classify Government acquisitions for supplies.  They also shall not be used by Federal government contractors when subcontracting for the acquisition for supplies.  The applicable manufacturing NAICS code shall be used to classify acquisitions for supplies.  A Wholesale Trade or Retail Trade business concern submitting an offer or a quote on a supply acquisition is categorized as a nonmanufacturer and deemed small if it has 500 or fewer employees and meets the requirements of 13 CFR 121.406.)
